    name: "Sobol's Total Indices for Accurate and Scalable Feature Exclusion in High-Dimensional Data",
    venue: 'BigData',
    year: '2025',
    direction: 'uq',
    tldr: 'A scalable Sobol-style feature exclusion framework for high-dimensional settings.',
    detail: 'This paper continues the uncertainty quantification line through global sensitivity analysis. The main thrust is to make Sobol-style total indices usable and accurate in high-dimensional settings, which matters for trustworthy interpretation and robust decision-making.',
    keywords: ['Sobol', 'feature exclusion', 'uncertainty quantification'],
    related: [
      { label: 'Higher-order decomposition', href: 'https://epubs.siam.org/doi/abs/10.1137/1.9781611977653.ch86' },
      { label: 'WSDM 2026 tutorial on UQ for graph dynamics', href: 'https://wsdm-conference.org/2026/index.php/tutorials/' }
    ],
    support: { label: 'Why sensitivity analysis matters', href: 'https://www.nist.gov/publications/global-sensitivity-analysis-primer' },
    href: 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?view_op=view_citation&citation_for_view=NC3-O6UAAAAJ:roLk4NBRz8UC',
    bibtex: `@inproceedings{zhang2025sobol, author = {Zhang, Zonghan and Chen, Zhiqian}, booktitle = {2025 IEEE International Conference on Big Data (BigData)}, title = {Sobol's Total Indices for Accurate and Scalable Feature Exclusion in High-Dimensional Data}, year = {2025}}`,
    image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1451187580459-43490279c0fa?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=80'
  },
  {
    slug: 'rashme-2025-vsv',
    name: 'Graph symbolic regression to interpret the propagation of Vesicular Stomatitis Virus across the US and Mexico',
    venue: 'SIGSPATIAL',
    year: '2025',
    direction: 'symbolic',
    tldr: 'Symbolic regression on graph-structured variables to make epidemic propagation mechanisms interpretable.',
    detail: 'This work pushes toward symbolic scientific discovery on graphs. Instead of stopping at black-box prediction, it uses symbolic regression to interpret how Vesicular Stomatitis Virus propagates across cross-border graph-structured systems in the US and Mexico.',
    keywords: ['symbolic regression', 'scientific discovery', 'epidemic graphs'],
    related: [
      { label: 'USDA storymap context', href: 'https://storymaps.arcgis.com/stories/4569acf3a05944c99360029dd7029a96' }
    ],
    support: { label: 'Animal disease propagation context', href: 'https://www.aphis.usda.gov/livestock-poultry-disease/cattle/vesicular-stomatitis' },
    href: 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?view_op=view_citation&citation_for_view=NC3-O6UAAAAJ:u-x6o8ySG0sC',
    bibtex: `@inproceedings{rashme2025graph, author = {Rashme, T. and Zhang, Z. and Weeks, J. and others and Chen, Zhiqian}, booktitle = {Proceedings of the 33rd ACM International Conference on Advances in Geographic Information Systems}, title = {Graph symbolic regression to interpret the propagation of Vesicular Stomatitis Virus across the US and Mexico}, year = {2025}}`,
    image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518152006812-edab29b069ac?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=80'
  },
  {
    slug: 'zhang-2025-interdiction',
    name: 'Network Interdiction Goes Neural',
    venue: 'KDD',
    year: '2025',
    direction: 'cross-network',
    tldr: 'A neural take on interdiction problems, connecting optimization under disruption to modern graph learning.',
    detail: 'This is a standalone but very interesting work that also connects well to the current cross-network interaction direction. Network interdiction is fundamentally about intervening under adversarial or constrained conditions, and this paper shows how neural methods can help with those difficult structured decisions.',
    keywords: ['network interdiction', 'graph optimization', 'neural combinatorial methods'],
    related: [
      { label: 'Multiplex influence maximization', href: 'https://ojs.aaai.org/index.php/AAAI/article/view/30255' }
    ],
    support: { label: 'Why critical-network intervention matters', href: 'https://www.nist.gov/el/cyber-physical-systems' },
    href: 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?view_op=view_citation&citation_for_view=NC3-O6UAAAAJ:WF5omc3nYNoC',
    bibtex: `@inproceedings{zhang2025interdiction, author = {Zhang, Lei and Chen, Zhiqian and Lu, Chang-Tien and Zhao, Liang}, booktitle = {Proceedings of the 31st ACM SIGKDD Conference on Knowledge Discovery and Data Mining}, title = {Network Interdiction Goes Neural}, year = {2025}}`,
    image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1450101499163-c8848c66ca85?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=80'
  },
  {
    slug: 'chen-2017-learning',
    name: 'Learning to fuse music genres with generative adversarial dual learning',
    venue: 'ICDM',
    year: '2017',
    direction: 'music-ai',
    tldr: 'A favorite personal project: genre fusion as a creative AI problem, not just a classification task.',
    detail: 'This remains one of my favorite projects. It treats music generation as genre fusion through adversarial dual learning, and even though I have not continued it yet, I still hope to revisit it with the right collaborators in music AI.',
    keywords: ['music AI', 'generative models', 'creative ML'],
    related: [
      { label: 'Fusion GAN repo', href: 'https://github.com/XGraph-Team/Fusion-GAN' }
    ],
    support: { label: 'Creative AI landscape', href: 'https://www.nature.com/articles/s41599-021-00865-3' },
    href: 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?view_op=view_citation&citation_for_view=NC3-O6UAAAAJ:d1gkVwhDpl0C',
    bibtex: `@inproceedings{chen2017learning, author = {Chen, Zhiqian and Wu, Chih-Wei and Lu, Yen-Cheng and Lerch, Alexander and Lu, Chang-Tien}, booktitle = {2017 IEEE International Conference on Data Mining (ICDM)}, organization = {IEEE}, pages = {817--822}, title = {Learning to fuse music genres with generative adversarial dual learning}, year = {2017}}`,
    image: 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aquastar/imczq/master/content/publication/chen-2017-learning/featured.png'
  }
];

---

<Layout title="Zhiqian Chen">
  <main class="container" id="top">
    <nav class="top-nav" aria-label="Sections">
      <button class="nav-toggle" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="mobile-nav-panel" aria-label="Open navigation menu">
        <span></span><span></span><span></span>
      </button>
      <div class="nav-links" id="mobile-nav-panel">
        <a href="/" aria-current="page">Home</a>
        <a href="/research">Research</a>
        <a href="/grant">Grant</a>
        <a href="/people">People</a>
        <a href="/teach">Teach</a>
        <a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=Zhiqian+Chen" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Paper <i class="ai ai-google-scholar-square ai-sm nav-ghost"></i> <i class="fas fa-arrow-up-right-from-square nav-ghost"></i></a>
        <a href="https://zhiqian.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Zhiqian's Note <i class="fas fa-arrow-up-right-from-square nav-ghost"></i></a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <section class="grid-2">
      <aside class="left-col">
        <article class="card module profile">
          <img class="avatar" src="https://imczq.com/authors/admin/avatar_huff586cc3096ffa7a7257f5a661abe783_130497_270x270_fill_q75_lanczos_center.jpg" alt="Zhiqian Chen" />
          <h1 class="name-en">Chen, Zhiqian</h1>
          <p class="name-zh">陈枳扦
            <span class="name-tip" tabindex="0" aria-label="Name meaning note">?
              <span class="tip-pop">物理含义：根据五行八卦算的</span>
            </span>
          </p>
          <p class="role">Assistant Professor · Mississippi State University</p>
          <p class="bio">I am an Assistant Professor of Computer Science &amp; Engineering at Mississippi State University, focusing on graph-structured intelligence for dynamic, uncertain, and knowledge-rich systems (see <a href="/research">details of my research interests</a>). I obtained my Ph.D. at Virginia Tech in 2020, under the supervision of Dr. Chang-Tien Lu. For students interested in me, check <a href="#connect-form">ways to work with me</a>. If interested in my courses, please check the <a href="/teach">course syllabi</a>.</p>

          <div class="icons" aria-label="social links">
            <a href="https://imczq.com/cv.pdf" title="CV"><i class="ai ai-cv"></i></a>
            <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=NC3-O6UAAAAJ" title="Google Scholar"><i class="ai ai-google-scholar"></i></a>
            <a href="https://github.com/aquastar" title="GitHub"><i class="fab fa-github"></i></a>
            <a href="https://twitter.com/imczq" title="X/Twitter"><i class="fab fa-square-x-twitter"></i></a>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/zhiqian-chen-ai/" title="LinkedIn"><i class="fab fa-linkedin"></i></a>
            <a href="https://www.zhihu.com/people/aquastar" title="Zhihu"><i class="fab fa-zhihu"></i></a>
            <a href="https://www.xiaohongshu.com/user/profile/64769efb000000001c029738" title="Xiaohongshu"><i class="fas fa-book"></i></a>
            <a href="https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4112-9647" title="ORCID"><i class="fab fa-orcid"></i></a>
            <a href="mailto:zchen@cse.msstate.edu" title="Email"><i class="fas fa-envelope"></i></a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card module">
          <h2>Recent Updates</h2>
          <ul class="updates" id="updates-list">
            {updates.map((u, idx) => (
              <li class={idx >= 10 ? 'update-hidden' : ''} data-extra-update={idx >= 10 ? 'true' : 'false'}>
                <span class={`tag ${u.type}`}>{u.type}</span>
                <span class="date-strong">{u.date}</span><span class="meta-inline" set:html={u.text}></span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
          {updates.length > 10 && (
            <button class="btn full updates-more" id="updates-more-btn" type="button">More</button>
          )}
        </article>
      </aside>

      <section class="right-col-main">
        <article class="card module rich hero-module" id="research">
          <h2>Research Statement</h2>
          <p class="lead">I study graph-structured intelligence for dynamic, uncertain, and knowledge-rich systems.</p>
          <div class="direction-visual">
            <img src="https://imczq.com/media/research_statement_hucb80f2447a0a6a816bf6ea6adae9c7ee_371656_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos_3.webp" alt="Research statement visual" />
          </div>
          <div class="statement-copy">
            <p>My goal is to understand how structure, interaction, and uncertainty shape decision-making across complex networks, from social and epidemiological systems to transportation, infrastructure, and emerging AI systems.</p>
            <p>My work combines spectral graph theory, uncertainty quantification, and cross-network modeling to build methods that are not only predictive, but also interpretable, transferable, and theoretically grounded. More broadly, I am interested in a general theory of graph dynamics that connects learning, inference, and control across interacting systems.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card module rich" id="selected-work">
          <h2>Selected</h2>
          <div class="direction-filter" id="direction-filter">
            <button class="filter-chip is-active" type="button" data-filter="all">All</button>
            {researchDirections.map((d) => (
              <button class="filter-chip" type="button" data-filter={d.key}>{d.label}</button>
            ))}
          </div>
          <p class="direction-desc" id="direction-desc">A cross-section of projects spanning theory, uncertainty, systems, and scientific discovery.</p>
          <div class="work-grid" id="selected-grid">
            {selectedWorks.map((p, idx) => (
              <article class="work-card" data-expand-card data-index={idx} data-direction={p.direction} data-name={p.name} data-venue={p.venue} data-year={p.year} data-tldr={p.tldr} data-detail={p.detail} data-keywords={p.keywords.join(' · ')} data-href={p.href} data-image={p.image} data-bibtex={p.bibtex} data-support-label={p.support.label} data-support-href={p.support.href} data-related={JSON.stringify(p.related)}>
                <img src={p.image || 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1515879218367-8466d910aaa4?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=80'} alt={p.name} />
                <div class="work-copy">
                  <div class="work-tags">
                    <span class="badge venue">{p.venue} {p.year}</span>
                  </div>
                  <h3>{p.name}</h3>
                  <p>{p.tldr}</p>
                  <div class="work-chips">
                    {p.keywords.slice(0, 2).map((kw) => <span class="mini-chip">{kw}</span>)}
                  </div>
                </div>
              </article>
            ))}
          </div>
          <div class="selected-detail-panel" id="selected-detail-panel" hidden>
            <div class="work-detail">
              <div class="work-detail-media">
                <img id="detail-image" src="" alt="" />
              </div>
              <div class="work-detail-copy">
                <div class="work-tags"><span class="badge venue" id="detail-venue"></span></div>
                <h3 id="detail-title"></h3>
                <p class="detail-tldr" id="detail-tldr"></p>
                <p id="detail-text"></p>
                <div class="detail-meta">
                  <span class="detail-label">Keywords</span>
                  <p class="work-keywords" id="detail-keywords"></p>
                </div>
                <div class="detail-meta">
                  <span class="detail-label">Why this direction matters</span>
                  <p class="detail-support"><a id="detail-support-link" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener"></a></p>
                </div>
                <div class="detail-meta">
                  <span class="detail-label">Related</span>
                  <div class="detail-related" id="detail-related"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="detail-actions">
                  <a class="detail-link" id="detail-link" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open paper</a>
                  <button class="detail-link" id="detail-bibtex-btn" type="button">Copy BibTeX</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>


        <article class="card module" id="github-projects">
          <h2>Tutorial-related Repos</h2>
          <div class="stack dense four-cols">
            {githubCards.map((repo) => (
              <article class="mini-card repo-card" data-href={repo.href} tabindex="0" role="link">
                <div class="row repo-top">
                  <h3>{repo.name}</h3>
                  <i class="fab fa-github repo-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <p>{repo.desc}</p>
                <div class="repo-meta repo-badges">
                  <img src={`https://img.shields.io/badge/${encodeURIComponent(repo.owner)}-f8fafc.svg?style=flat-square&logo=github&logoColor=181717&labelColor=f8fafc&color=f8fafc`} alt={`owner ${repo.owner}`} />
                  <img src={`https://img.shields.io/badge/${encodeURIComponent(repo.language)}-f8fafc.svg?style=flat-square&logo=python&logoColor=3776AB&labelColor=f8fafc&color=f8fafc`} alt={`language ${repo.language}`} />
                  <iframe class="github-star-btn" src={`https://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=${repo.owner}&repo=${repo.repo}&type=star&count=true&size=small`} title={`Star ${repo.name} on GitHub`} width="96" height="20"></iframe>
                </div>
              </article>
            ))}
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card module ghost-card" id="ghost-entries">
          <h2>Tech Notes</h2>
          <div class="stack dense four-cols">
            {ghostEntries.map((entry) => (
              <div class="mini-card note-card placeholder">
                <div class="row"><h3>{entry.title}</h3><span class="repo-pill muted">{entry.meta}</span></div>
                <p>{entry.desc}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
  </main>

  <script>
    const selectedCards = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-expand-card]'));
    const detailPanel = document.getElementById('selected-detail-panel');
    const selectedGrid = document.getElementById('selected-grid');
    const detailImage = document.getElementById('detail-image');
    const detailVenue = document.getElementById('detail-venue');
    const detailTitle = document.getElementById('detail-title');
    const detailTldr = document.getElementById('detail-tldr');
    const detailText = document.getElementById('detail-text');
    const detailKeywords = document.getElementById('detail-keywords');
    const detailLink = document.getElementById('detail-link');
    const detailBibtexBtn = document.getElementById('detail-bibtex-btn');
    const detailSupportLink = document.getElementById('detail-support-link');
    const detailRelated = document.getElementById('detail-related');
    const directionFilter = document.getElementById('direction-filter');
    const directionDesc = document.getElementById('direction-desc');
    const mobileQuery = window.matchMedia('(max-width: 720px)');
    const navToggle = document.querySelector('.nav-toggle');
    const topNav = document.querySelector('.top-nav');
    const updatesMoreBtn = document.getElementById('updates-more-btn');
    let closeTimer;
    let activeIndex = -1;

    navToggle?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const open = topNav?.classList.toggle('nav-open');
      navToggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', open ? 'true' : 'false');
    });

    document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a').forEach((link) => {
      link.addEventListener('click', () => {
        topNav?.classList.remove('nav-open');
        navToggle?.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
      });
    });

    updatesMoreBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-extra-update="true"]').forEach((el) => {
        el.classList.remove('update-hidden');
      });
      updatesMoreBtn.remove();
    });

    function resetCards() {
      selectedCards.forEach((c) => c.classList.remove('is-expanded'));
      selectedGrid?.classList.remove('has-expanded');
      activeIndex = -1;
    }

    function collapseDetail(animated = true) {
      window.clearTimeout(closeTimer);
      resetCards();
      if (detailPanel.hidden) return;
      if (!animated) {
        detailPanel.hidden = true;
        detailPanel.classList.remove('is-collapsing');
        return;
      }
      detailPanel.classList.remove('is-collapsing');
      void detailPanel.offsetWidth;
      detailPanel.classList.add('is-collapsing');
      closeTimer = window.setTimeout(() => {
        detailPanel.hidden = true;
        detailPanel.classList.remove('is-collapsing');
      }, 220);
    }

    function expandCard(card, idx) {
      window.clearTimeout(closeTimer);
      resetCards();
      activeIndex = idx;
      card.classList.add('is-expanded');
      selectedGrid?.classList.add('has-expanded');
      detailImage.src = card.dataset.image || '';
      detailImage.alt = card.dataset.name || '';
      detailVenue.textContent = `${card.dataset.venue || ''} ${card.dataset.year || ''}`.trim();
      detailTitle.textContent = card.dataset.name || '';
      detailTldr.textContent = card.dataset.tldr || '';
      detailText.textContent = card.dataset.detail || '';
      detailKeywords.textContent = card.dataset.keywords || '';
      detailLink.href = card.dataset.href || '#';
      detailBibtexBtn.onclick = async () => {
        try {
          await navigator.clipboard.writeText(card.dataset.bibtex || '');
          detailBibtexBtn.textContent = 'Copied!';
          setTimeout(() => { detailBibtexBtn.textContent = 'Copy BibTeX'; }, 1200);
        } catch {}
      };
      detailSupportLink.href = card.dataset.supportHref || '#';
      detailSupportLink.textContent = card.dataset.supportLabel || '';
      detailRelated.innerHTML = '';
      try {
        const related = JSON.parse(card.dataset.related || '[]');
        related.forEach((r) => {
          const a = document.createElement('a');
          a.href = r.href || '#';
          a.target = '_blank';
          a.rel = 'noopener';
          a.textContent = r.label;
          a.className = 'related-link';
          detailRelated.appendChild(a);
        });
      } catch {}
      const visibleCards = selectedCards.filter((c) => c.style.display !== 'none');
      const currentVisibleIndex = visibleCards.indexOf(card);
      const cardsPerRow = mobileQuery.matches ? 1 : (window.innerWidth <= 1200 ? 2 : 3);
      const rowStart = Math.floor(currentVisibleIndex / cardsPerRow) * cardsPerRow;
      const rowEnd = Math.min(rowStart + cardsPerRow, visibleCards.length);
      const anchor = visibleCards[rowEnd - 1] || card;
      anchor.insertAdjacentElement('afterend', detailPanel);
      detailPanel.classList.remove('is-collapsing');
      detailPanel.hidden = false;
    }

    selectedCards.forEach((card, idx) => {
      card.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => {
        if (mobileQuery.matches) return;
        expandCard(card, idx);
      });
      card.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
        if (mobileQuery.matches) return;
        closeTimer = window.setTimeout(() => collapseDetail(true), 120);
      });
      card.addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (!mobileQuery.matches) return;
        if (activeIndex === idx) collapseDetail(true);
        else expandCard(card, idx);
      });
    });

    detailPanel.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => {
      if (!mobileQuery.matches) window.clearTimeout(closeTimer);
    });
    detailPanel.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
      if (!mobileQuery.matches) collapseDetail(true);
    });

    directionFilter?.querySelectorAll('[data-filter]').forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const key = btn.getAttribute('data-filter') || 'all';
        directionFilter.querySelectorAll('[data-filter]').forEach((b) => b.classList.remove('is-active'));
        btn.classList.add('is-active');
        const directionMap = Object.fromEntries(Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.filter-chip[data-filter]')).map((el) => [el.getAttribute('data-filter'), el.textContent]));
        const descriptions = {
          'all': 'A cross-section of projects spanning theory, uncertainty, systems, and scientific discovery.',
          'materials': 'Machine learning for scientific discovery and energy-storage materials.',
          'unified-graph': 'Toward unified operator-level views that connect spectral, spatial, and dynamical graph learning.',
          'uq': 'Reliable graph decisions under uncertainty, sensitivity, and limited observations.',
          'hw-sw': 'Learning systems that connect machine learning with circuits, architecture, and systems constraints.',
          'music-ai': 'Generative and multimodal systems for computational creativity and music understanding.',
          'innovation': 'Forecasting scientific and technological impact with graph- and context-aware models.',
          'cross-network': 'Optimization and intervention when multiple interacting networks matter at once.',
          'software': 'Understanding and improving ML systems for software analysis and security tasks.',
          'symbolic': 'Interpretable symbolic models for scientific mechanisms on graph-structured systems.',
          'drone': 'Distributed systems and planning infrastructure for autonomous drone applications.'
        };
        directionDesc.textContent = descriptions[key] || descriptions['all'];
        selectedCards.forEach((card) => {
          const show = key === 'all' || card.dataset.direction === key;
          card.style.display = show ? '' : 'none';
        });
        collapseDetail(false);
      });
    });

    document.querySelectorAll('.repo-card[data-href]').forEach((card) => {
      card.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
        const target = event.target;
        if (target instanceof Element && target.closest('.github-star-btn')) return;
        const href = card.getAttribute('data-href');
        if (href) window.open(href, '_blank', 'noopener');
      });
      card.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
        if (event.key === 'Enter' || event.key === ' ') {
          event.preventDefault();
          const href = card.getAttribute('data-href');
          if (href) window.open(href, '_blank', 'noopener');
        }
      });
    });

    document.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
      if (detailPanel.hidden || !mobileQuery.matches) return;
      const target = event.target;
      if (target instanceof Node) {
        const insideCard = target.closest('[data-expand-card]');
        const insideDetail = target.closest('#selected-detail-panel');
        if (!insideCard && !insideDetail) collapseDetail(true);
      }
    });
  </script>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --accent: #2563eb; --accent-soft: #dbeafe; --ink: #0f172a; --muted: #475569; --page: #ffffff; }
  body { background: var(--page); }
  .container { max-width: 1800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }
  .card { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.92); border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.12); border-radius: 18px; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(15,23,42,0.06); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); }
  .top-nav { margin-bottom: 14px; padding: 10px 0 14px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; gap: 12px; background: transparent; border: none; border-bottom: none; border-radius: 0; box-shadow: none; position: relative; }
  .nav-links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; }
  .top-nav a { text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink); font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif; font-size: 0.9rem; padding: 7px 10px; border-radius: 999px; background: transparent; }
  .nav-toggle { display: none; width: 40px; height: 40px; border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.18); border-radius: 12px; background: #fff; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; cursor: pointer; box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(15,23,42,0.05); }
